  "response": "According to traditional accounts, Gautama Buddha died around 483 BCE at the age of 80 in Kushinagar, located in present-day Uttar Pradesh, India. He is said to have died from a combination of old age and food poisoning after eating a meal prepared by a blacksmith named Cunda. His last words reportedly urged his followers to continue seeking enlightenment and to work diligently towards their own spiritual liberation. After his death, his body was cremated and his ashes were distributed among various communities, who built stupas to enshrine them. This event is known as the Parinirvana or \"final nirvana\" of the Buddha, signifying his complete release from the cycle of rebirth.",
